cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper deals with the detection of RF jamming attacks in vehicular ad-hoc networks (VANET), which are a subset of wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for detection, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The topic of security and defense against attacks suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of supervised learning algorithms also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
